(194, 26, 'es_builder_private', '\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n			<article data-ix="article-151276230591667339" data-clickable="true" class=""><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151276230783588593" data-clickable="true"><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151276231347265714" data-clickable="true">col-xsmall-8 <div class="editable_item no-margins" data-ix="column-151276231347265714_content"><p>Add element</p><input name="column-content-editor" id="column-content-editor" type="text" data-ix="column-151276231347265714_hidden" hidden="hidden" value="<h2>Add element</h2><p>Trigger calls events during scrolling on scene. The element contains 2 attributes. Name and margin top. You have to create tigger and add to enedScroll function. It should looks like example below.</p><p>[js]var trigger = new enedScroll.Trigger( @name, @marginTop )[/js]</p>"></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 specification" data-ix="column-151276233006317832" data-clickable="true">col-xsmall-8 <div class="editable_item no-margins" data-ix="column-151276233006317832_content"><p>Specification</p><input name="column-content-editor" id="column-content-editor" type="text" data-ix="column-151276233006317832_hidden" hidden="hidden" value="<p>[header]</p><h3>Specification</h3><p>[/header]</p>"></div><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151276244414121953" data-clickable="true"><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151276245617875755" data-clickable="true">col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3 <div class="editable_item no-margins" data-ix="column-151276245617875755_content"><p>Name</p><input name="column-content-editor" id="column-content-editor" type="text" data-ix="column-151276245617875755_hidden" hidden="hidden" value="<h3>Name</h3>"></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151276246094751184" data-clickable="true">col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 <div class="editable_item no-margins" data-ix="column-1512762460947