(242, 439, 'es_builder_output', '[[{"class":"cols","children":[{"class":"col-xsmall-8 ","content":"<h2>License</h2><p>The enedScroll is subject to the license selected when purchasing the product.</p><p><a class="inline" href="https://codecanyon.net/licenses/standard">Read more about Envato licenses</a></p><p><a class="inline" href="https://codecanyon.net/licenses/faq">FAQ Envato licenses</a></p>"}]}],[{"class":"cols","children":[{"class":"col-xsmall-8 ","content":"<h2>Installing</h2><p>To get started with enedScroll you need jQuery version &lt; 1.x.x and enedScroll files.</p><p>Before [markup]&lt;/body&gt;[/markup] tag you should include once of enedScroll version, normall or minifed. You can use code below.</p><p>[code]&lt;script src="enedScroll.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;[/code]</p>"}]}],[{"class":"cols","children":[{"class":"col-xsmall-8 ","content":"<h2 class="title">Trigger</h2><p>This is a magic wand with which you can determine when to call your scene. For a more detailed description of Trigger you will find it here <em><strong>{{ a > trigger – add element }}</strong></em>.</p>"}]}],[{"class":"cols","children":[{"class":"col-xsmall-8 ","content":"<h2 class="title">Selectors</h2><p>Selectors as trigger can determine moment to call your event.</p><p>Exists 2 selectors, top and bottom. Specifies a moment of a function call is based on the element that was assigned to the scene as a target.</p>"}]}],[{"class":"cols","children":[{"class":"col-xsmall-8 ","content":"<h2 class="title">Scene</h2><p>It is basic space to create animations. All parameters like duration are connected with scene parameters.</p>"}]}]]'),
