iable</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i> <i class="lighting">object</i> <i class="lighting">number</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Required</p></div>";}i:6;O:8:"stdClass":1:{s:5:"class";s:5:"clear";}i:7;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:13:"col-xsmall-8 ";s:7:"content";s:3090:"<h2>Variables in other functions</h2><p>If you want to read variable of transition layer from e.g. add function you may use <code class=" language-markup">scene.var(name)</code>.</p><p>Where a name is an @variable which you gave before in a some function. How you should do it, see in structure function.</p><h4> </h4><h4>scene.add</h4><pre class=" language-javascript"><code class=" language-javascript"><span class="token punctuation">[</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> css_property<span class="token punctuation">:</span> css_property_value<span class="token punctuation">,</span> … <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> duration<span class="token punctuation">,</span> offset<span class="token punctuation">,</span> @variable <span class="token punctuation">]</span></code></pre><p>Returns: <em><i class="lighting">duration  </i><i class="lighting">name  </i><i class="lighting">offset</i>  <i class="lighting">offset_done </i><i class="lighting">real_duration </i><i class="lighting">real_offset</i></em></p><p> </p><h4>scene.pin</h4><pre class=" language-javascript"><code class=" language-javascript"><span class="token punctuation">[</span> duration<span class="token punctuation">,</span> offset<span class="token punctuation">,</span> @variable <span class="token punctuation">]</span></code></pre><p>Returns: <i class="lighting">pin_done </i><i class="lighting">pin_duration </i><i class="lighting">pin_global_offset </i><i class="lighting">pin_offset</i></p><p> </p><h4>scene.setPoint</h4><pre class=" language-javascript"><code class=" language-javascript">duration<span class="token punctuation">,</span> offset<span class="token punctuation">,</span> @name</code></pre><p>Returns: <i class="lighting">point_duration </i><i class="lighting">point_offset</i></p><p> </p><h4>scene.repeat</h4><pre class=" language-javascript"><code class=" language-javascript"><span class="token punctuation">[</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> css_property<span class="token punctuation">:</span> css_property_value<span class="token punctuation">,</span> … <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span>duration<span class="token punctuation">,</span>repeat_duration<span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span>offset<span class="token punctuation">,</span>repeat_offset<span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> @variable <span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> … <span class="token punctuation">]</span></code></pre><p>Returns collection of layers with: <em><i class="lighting">duration  </i><i class="lighting">name  </i><i class="lighting">offset</i>  <i class="lighting">offset_done </i><i class="lighting">real_duration</i><i class="lighting">real_offset</i></em></p>";}i:8;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:13:"col-xsmall-8 ";s:7:"content";s:3413:"<h2>Examples</h2><pre class=" language-javascript"><code class=" language-javascript">scene<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token keyword">var</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span> <span class="token string">jump</span> <span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">// Returns undefined</span>\nscene<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token keyword">var</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span> <span class="token string">jump</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> no<span class="token operator">-</span>bored <span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\nscene<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token keyword">var</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span> <span class="token string">jump</span> <span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">// Returns no-bored</span>\n\nscene<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">add</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span> <span class="token function">$</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span>element<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span>\n    <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span> opacity<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token number">1</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> color<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token function">rgb</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token number">255</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token number">255</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token number">255</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">0.2</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token string">opacity</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\nscene<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token keyword">var</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span> <span class="token string">opacity</span> <span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment">// Returns [ duration: 0.2, name: opacity, offset: 0, offset_done: 0.2, real_duration: 0.2, real_offset: 0 ]</span></code></pre>";}}}}i:6;a:2:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:4:"cols";s:8:"children";a:1:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:13:"col-xsmall-8 ";s:7:"content";s:197:"<h2>Is</h2><p>Calling a function by reaching the appropriate state for a specified transition by the variable name of a transition.</p><p>[js]scene.is( @variable_name, @events, @callback )[/js]</p>";}}}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:18:"cols specification";s:8:"children";a:11:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:18:"col-xsmall-8 title";s:7:"content";s:57:"<p> </p><header><h3>Specification</h3></header><p> </p>";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:25:"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 ";s:7:"content";s:22:"<h3>Variable name</h3>";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:30:"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break";s:7:"content";s:2146:"<header><p>It is an @name or @variable of transition layer, point which you gave before in a some function. How you should do it, see in structure function.</p></header><p>If you assigned a name in [markup]scene.repeat[/markup]</p><pre class="  language-javascript"><code class="  language-javascript">scene<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">repeat</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> transform<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token function">scale</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">1</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token number">2</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0.6</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">0.4</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token number">0.6</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span><span class="token number">0</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> scaling <span class="token punctuation">]</span> <span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token number">2</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span></code></pre><p>for a layer your @variable_name in this function should looks like <strong><em>scaling{index}</em></strong> where index is ( integer ) number of collection. Scan by [markup]scene.var[/markup] the <strong><em>scaling</em> </strong>so you will understand using of index. Other way your @variable_name should be just an <strong><em>scaling</em></strong>.</p><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Required</p></div>";}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":1:{s:5:"class";s:5:"clear";}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:25:"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 ";s:7:"content";s:15:"<h3>Events</h3>";}i:5;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:30:"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break";s:7:"content";s:607:"<header><p>States which call callback.</p><p>Available states: <i class="lighting">BEFORE</i>, <i class="lighting">AFTER</i>, <i class="lighting">ENTER</i>, <i class="lighting">UPDATE</i></p></header><p>Events make single call the callback: <i class="lighting">BEFORE</i>, <i class="lighting">AFTER</i>, <i class="lighting">ENTER</i>.</p><p><i class="lighting">UPDATE </i>state call the callback every scroll by reaching the appropriate space.</p><p> </p><p>You can join states toghether.</p><p> </p><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Required</p></div>";}i:6;O:8:"stdClass":1:{s:5:"class";s:5:"clear";}i:7;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:25:"col-xsmall-8 col-small-3 ";s:7:"content";s:17:"<h3>Callback</h3>";}i:8;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:30:"col-xsmall-8 col-small-5 break";s:7:"content";s:312:"<header><p>A function which is called.</p></header><p>The function returns <i class="lighting">progress </i><i class="lighting">state </i><i class="lighting">var</i></p><p>[js]function(e){}[/js]</p><div class="row"><p> </p><p>Type <i class="lighting">function</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Required</p></div>";}i:9;O:8:"stdClass":1:{s:5:"class";s:5:"clear";}i:10;O:8:"stdClass":2:{s:5:"class";s:13:"col-xsmall-8 ";s:7:"content";s:221:"<h2>Example</h2>\n[js]scene.setPoint( 0.5, 0,bueno );\nscene.is( (string) bueno, (string) ENTER, BEFORE, function(e){\n  console.log(e);\n});\nscene.is( (string) bueno, (string) UPDATE, function(e){\n  console.log(e);\n});\n[/js]";}}}}}');
