(26, 1, '2017-11-24 23:31:56', '2017-11-24 22:31:56', '<article data-ix="article-151276230591667339"><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151276230783588593"><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151276231347265714"><div data-ix="column-151276231347265714_item" editor-item=""><h2>Add element</h2><p>Trigger calls events during scrolling on scene. The element contains 2 attributes. Name and margin top. You have to create tigger and add to enedScroll function. It should looks like example below.</p><p>[js]var trigger = new enedScroll.Trigger( @name, @marginTop )[/js]</p></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 specification" data-ix="column-151276233006317832"><div data-ix="column-151276233006317832_item" editor-item=""><p>[header]</p><h3>Specification</h3><p>[/header]</p></div><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151276244414121953"><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151276245617875755"><div data-ix="column-151276245617875755_item" editor-item=""><h3>Name</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151276246094751184"><div data-ix="column-151276246094751184_item" editor-item=""><header>Shows the name above the trigger.</header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Default <i class="lighting">null</i></p></div></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151276256055427520"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-15127625649032664"><div data-ix="column-15127625649032664_item" editor-item=""><h3>Margin top</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151276256899893933"><div data-ix="column-151276256899893933_item" editor-item=""><header><p>Margin from top allowing adjust moment of call event.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">integer</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Default <i class="lighting">0</i></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></article>', 'Create Trigger', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'create-trigger', '', '', '2018-01-23 12:07:46', '2018-01-23 11:07:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/enedScroll%20-%20build/docs/?page_id=26', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(28, 1, '2017-11-24 23:32:04', '2017-11-24 22:32:04', '<article data-ix="article-1512809423483100851"><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151280942797462363"><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151280943260567717"><div data-ix="column-151280943260567717_item" editor-item=""><h2>Description</h2><p>The function create new scene and it is preparing container of functions which allow you to create actions. The function is connecting all values, target as scene, trigger, selectors and visual. You can use the function by following the example below.</p><p>[js] var scene = new enedScroll( @target [, @trigger [, @options ] ] );&nbsp; [/js]</p></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 specification" data-ix="column-151280971162345414"><div data-ix="column-151280971162345414_item" editor-item=""><header><h3>Specification</h3></header></div><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151280974256422832"><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151280975355269828"><div data-ix="column-151280975355269828_item" editor-item=""><h3>Target</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151280975911936762"><div data-ix="column-151280975911936762_item" editor-item=""><header><p>It is element which is the point of reference for offset and duration. All these values ​​will be suggesting by the target''s properties. E.g. Integer 0 for offset means offset of the target. Above it is described as scene.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string </i><i class="lighting">object</i></p></div><p>[js]$(my-item)[/js]</p><p>[js].my-item[/js]</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151280976091993200"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151280988386319428"><div data-ix="column-151280988386319428_item" editor-item=""><h3>Trigger</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151280988814854305"><div data-ix="column-151280988814854305_item" editor-item=""><header><p>Here you add trigger, easiest way is by variable. Read about trigger. If is empty then enedScroll create default trigger with margin top equals <i class="lighting">0</i>.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">object</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Default <i class="lighting">0</i></p></div><p>[js]new enedScroll.Trigger[/js]</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151280988963514993"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151280989615921256"><div data-ix="column-151280989615921256_item" editor-item=""><h3>Options</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151280989898165672"><div data-ix="column-151280989898165672_item" editor-item=""><header><p>It consists of two keys, selectors and visual. Read about selectors Read about visual.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">object</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Selectors default <i class="lighting">[0,0]</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Visual default <i class="lighting">{ }</i></p></div><p>[code]{<br> selectors: @selectors_options,<br> visual: @visual_options<br> }[/code]</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151280990293392073"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-15128099130966594"><div data-ix="column-15128099130966594_item" editor-item=""><h2>Example</h2><p>Full build of function</p><p>[js]new enedScroll( $(''.element''), trigger, { selectors: [0,0], visual: visual_defaults });[/js]</p><p>Where trigger and visual_defaults are variables.</p></div></div></div></div></div></article>', 'Calling enedScroll', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'calling-enedscroll', '', '', '2018-01-23 22:25:07', '2018-01-23 21:25:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/enedScroll%20-%20build/docs/?page_id=28', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(30, 1, '2017-11-24 23:32:13', '2017-11-24 22:32:13', '<article data-ix="article-151285230032780904"><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151285230167739953"><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151285230828945736"><div data-ix="column-151285230828945736_item" editor-item=""><h2>Add</h2><p>Make transitions between values for css properties.</p><p>[js]scene.add( @element, @transitions, @delay );[/js]</p></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 specification" data-ix="column-151285231000972324"><div data-ix="column-151285231000972324_item" editor-item=""><header><h3>Specification</h3></header></div><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151285308816537387"><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285309344713448"><div data-ix="column-151285309344713448_item" editor-item=""><h3>Element</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151285310569330910"><div data-ix="column-151285310569330910_item" editor-item=""><header><p>It is item which we want to manipulate.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">object</i></p></div><p>[js]$(.item)[/js]</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285311309812802"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 column" data-ix="column-151285313802311814"><div data-ix="column-151285313802311814_item" editor-item=""><h3>Transitions</h3><p>It is set of css values which you want to change with scrolling.</p><p>[js]&nbsp;<br>[<br>&nbsp; [ [ { css_property: css_property_value, ... }, duration, offset ], <br>&nbsp; ... <br>] <br>[/js]</p></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-15128531457521346"><div data-ix="column-15128531457521346_item" editor-item=""><h5>css_property</h5></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151285314978271298"><div data-ix="column-151285314978271298_item" editor-item=""><header><p>It is css attribute e.g. opacity, transform. Color attribute supports only rgb, rgba</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285316383299553"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285316835593692"><div data-ix="column-151285316835593692_item" editor-item=""><h5>css_property_value</h5></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151285317179134847"><div data-ix="column-151285317179134847_item" editor-item=""><header><p>It is css attribute value. Takes from to value.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285317503122808"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285318062082976"><div data-ix="column-151285318062082976_item" editor-item=""><h5>Duration</h5></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151285318381067052"><div data-ix="column-151285318381067052_item" editor-item=""><header><p>Duration of transition.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">integer </i><i class="lighting">string</i></p><p>Integer <i class="lighting">0.1 = 100</i><br>String <i class="lighting">100 = 100</i><br>String <i class="lighting">50% = 50%</i></p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp;of scene</p></div></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285318504068017"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285318744223594"><div data-ix="column-151285318744223594_item" editor-item=""><h5>Offset</h5></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-15128531903236547"><div data-ix="column-15128531903236547_item" editor-item=""><header><p>Offset of transition. The offset is added to previous transition offset.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">integer </i><i class="lighting">string</i></p><p>Integer <i class="lighting">0.1 = 100</i><br>String <i class="lighting">100 = 100</i><br>String <i class="lighting">50% = 50% </i><br>&nbsp; of scene</p></div></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285322678039610"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285322976672077"><div data-ix="column-151285322976672077_item" editor-item=""><h3>Delay</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151285323275744969"><div data-ix="column-151285323275744969_item" editor-item=""><header><p>Delay between next item. If element has length &gt; 1 then you can add delay between next item transitions</p></header><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div><div class="row"><p>Default <i class="lighting">0</i></p></div><p>&nbsp; E.g. +0.1</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285323663776996"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151285323944985261"><div data-ix="column-151285323944985261_item" editor-item=""><h2>Examples</h2><p>[js] scene.add( $(''.element''), [</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[{ opacity: [0,1], color: rgb([0,255],[0,255],[0,255]) }, 0.2, 0],</p><p>]);[/js]</p><p>[js] scene.add( $(''.element''), [</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[{ opacity: [0,1] }, 0.2, 0],</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[{ transform: rotate([0,360]deg) }, 0.2, 0.1], // ( Auto offset =&gt; prev offset + prev duration + this offset )</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[{ transform: translateX([0,100)px) translateY([0,100]px), opacity: [1,0] }, 0.2, 0], // ( Auto offset =&gt; prev offset + prev duration + this offset )</p><p>]);[/js]</p></div></div></div></div></div></article><article data-ix="article-151285530428413357"><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151285530733340936"><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151285531337835756"><div data-ix="column-151285531337835756_item" editor-item=""><h2>Pin</h2><p>Create pinning. Using timeline sytem you can create multi pins.</p><p>[js]&nbsp;scene.pin( @element, @timeline ); [/js]</p></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 specification" data-ix="column-151285559723074563"><div data-ix="column-151285559723074563_item" editor-item=""><header><h3>Specification</h3></header></div><div class="cols" data-ix="row-151285562698322203"><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285565485312829"><div data-ix="column-151285565485312829_item" editor-item=""><h3>Element</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5 column" data-ix="column-151285565968493324"><div data-ix="column-151285565968493324_item" editor-item=""><header><p>It is item which you want to pin.</p></header><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">object</i></p></div><p>[js]$(.item)[/js]</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285566100250158"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-3" data-ix="column-151285566410628983"><div data-ix="column-151285566410628983_item" editor-item=""><h3>Timeline</h3></div></div><div class="col-xsmall-8 col-medium-5" data-ix="column-151285566733917234"><div data-ix="column-151285566733917234_item" editor-item=""><p>It is set of another sets which contains values of pin.</p><p>Each set in a @timeline is called pin. For better understanding.</p><p>[js][ // start timeline</p><p>[ duration, offset, @variable ], // pin</p><p>[ duration, offset, @variable ],&nbsp;// pin</p><p>....</p><p>][/js]</p><p>Every pin has&nbsp;<i class="lighting">Auto offset =&gt; prev pin''s offset + prev pin''s duration + that pin offset</i></p><h5>&nbsp;</h5><h5>@Vartiable</h5><div class="row"><p>Type <i class="lighting">string</i></p></div><p>It is variable which contains parameters of the pin from timeline. You can get the set of the parameters by <strong>var function</strong>.</p></div></div><div class="clear" data-ix="clear-151285668999251768"></div><div class="col-xsmall-8" data-ix="column-151285669361132855"><div data-ix="column-151285669361132855_item" editor-item=""><h2>Example</h2><p>[js] var timeline = [</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[ 0.4, 0],</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[ 0.35, 0, ″second-pin″],</p><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;[ 0.35, 0.2 ]</p><p>];</p><p>scene.pin( $(element), timeline );[/js]</p></div></div></div></div></div></article>', 'Essential functions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'essential-functions', '', '', '2019-09-02 19:33:52', '2019-09-02 17:33:52', '', 0, 'http://localhost/enedScroll%20-%20build/docs/?page_id=30', 0, 'page', '', 0),
